1. Definitions
"Original Work" means the software, source code, and associated documentation initially released under this License.

"Derivative Work" means any modification, adaptation, translation, or enhancement of the Original Work.

"Distribution" means any act of sharing, selling, or providing access to the Work to third parties.

"SaaS Provision" means providing the functionality of the Work to users over a network (Software as a Service).

"Age-Restricted Jurisdictions" refers to any country or sovereign territory that mandates age verification or identity "gatekeeping" specifically for the installation or use of Operating Systems (OSes) at the kernel or system level (distinct from general internet content filtering).

